source: crates/acetone-cli/tests/help_snapshots.rs
expression: combined
---
### unknown-subcommand
argv:   acetone nonesuch
status: 2
stderr: error: unrecognized subcommand 'nonesuch'

Usage: acetone [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

For more information, try '--help'.

### ambiguous-prefix
argv:   acetone c
status: 2
stderr: error: unrecognized subcommand 'c'

  tip: some similar subcommands exist: 'checkout', 'commit', 'schema', 'cypher'

Usage: acetone [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

For more information, try '--help'.

### missing-colon-label
argv:   acetone query CREATE (Topic {name: 'First'});
status: 1
stderr: error: cannot persist node: this node has no labels — in Cypher a label is written with a colon, e.g. `(:Topic {…})`; a bare name like `(Topic {…})` is a variable, not a label

### schema-not-declared
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Widget {sku: 'a'});
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 8: unknown label 'Widget' (declared labels come from the schema map)

### parse-error
argv:   acetone query MATCH (n) RETRUN n
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 11: expected a clause (MATCH, OPTIONAL MATCH, UNWIND, WITH, RETURN, CALL, CREATE, SET, REMOVE, DELETE or DETACH DELETE), found 'RETRUN'

### rel-missing-colon
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Topic {name: 'a'})-[LINK]->(:Topic {name: 'b'});
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 28: CREATE requires a relationship type — write it with a colon, e.g. `[:LINK]`; a bare `[LINK]` is a variable, not a type

### rel-multiple-types
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Topic {name: 'a'})-[:LINK|OTHER]->(:Topic {name: 'b'});
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 28: CREATE requires exactly one relationship type

### rel-unknown-type
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Topic {name: 'a'})-[:NOPE]->(:Topic {name: 'b'});
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 28: unknown relationship type 'NOPE' — declare it first with `acetone declare-rel-type "NOPE"`

### duplicate-key
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Topic {name: 'x'});
status: 1
stderr: error: CREATE of "Topic" ["x"] conflicts with an existing node; CREATE always makes a new node, so identity collides (a MERGE on a multi-element pattern also CREATEs its nodes when the whole pattern doesn't match). To match-or-create, MERGE each node on its own before MERGEing a relationship between them: `MERGE (a:Label {…}) MERGE (b:…) MERGE (a)-[:…]->(b)`

### duplicate-key-in-statement
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Topic {name: 'y'}) CREATE (:Topic {name: 'y'});
status: 1
stderr: error: CREATE creates the node "Topic" ["y"] twice in the same statement; each CREATE makes a new node and identity must be unique

### get-node-not-found
argv:   acetone get-node Topic missing
status: 1
stderr: error: not found

### rekey-missing-node
argv:   acetone rekey Topic absent present -m r
status: 1
stderr: error: rekeying "Topic" ["absent"]: no node "Topic" with key ["absent"]

### label-did-you-mean
argv:   acetone query MATCH (n:Hsot) RETURN n
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 7: unknown label 'Hsot' (declared labels come from the schema map) — did you mean "Host"?

### function-did-you-mean
argv:   acetone query RETURN toUppr('a')
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 8: unknown function 'toUppr' — did you mean "toUpper"?

### skip-string-bound
argv:   acetone query MATCH (n:Topic) RETURN n SKIP 'x'
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 31: invalid argument: SKIP/LIMIT needs a non-negative integer, got "x"

### limit-string-bound
argv:   acetone query MATCH (n:Topic) RETURN n LIMIT 'x'
status: 1
stderr: error: line 1, column 32: invalid argument: SKIP/LIMIT needs a non-negative integer, got "x"

### labelled-no-key
argv:   acetone query CREATE (:Solo {x: 1});
status: 1
stderr: error: cannot persist node: none of the labels ["Solo"] declares a key, so this node has no identity (Invariant #3) — declare one first, e.g. `acetone declare-label "Solo" --key <property>`
